<h1>@HI{{hajimeru}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vmasustem{{}}<strong>@HI{{hajimeru}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{hajimeru}}</strong> is attached as a suffix to the @HI{{masu}}-stem of verbs to mean that someone or something 
begins to be in  some state.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{eight^month}}kara@KJ{{source^family*name^thing^word}}wo@KJ{{read}}mi<strong>hajimemashita</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I began to read <em>The Tale of Genji</em> in August.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{hajimeru}}</strong> can be attached to a punctual verb as long as the subject is plural.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{person^noma}}ga@KJ{{meeting^location}}ni@KJ{{don}}ki<strong>hajimemashita</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      People began to arrive at the meeting room.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

